1
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:14,097
I think I got everything.

2
00:00:14,264 --> 00:00:18,059
If I forgot anything,
I'll just figure it out on the way.

3
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:20,186
-You're back on Thursday?
-Thursday. Yeah.

4
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:23,648
Unless we break down in Amarillo.

5
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:30,447
Kim, I want you to know...

6
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:33,324
...I don't take this for granted.

7
00:00:33,491 --> 00:00:35,577
It means a lot.

8
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:39,664
I'll see you Thursday.

9
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:40,368
Can I sit here?

10
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:43,705
Sure, man.

11
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:46,082
Just a word of warning...

12
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:51,254
...I had a pile of cheese-chili fries
back at Stuckey's, with onions on top.

13
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:53,590
Last guy who sat here
didn't last five miles.

14
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:57,594
But, you know, welcome to it.

15
00:03:56,361 --> 00:03:58,363
Jynetta.

16
00:03:58,529 --> 00:04:00,490
Very nice,
I like the hearts over the I's.

17
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,867
-This is a real nice touch.
-Thank you.

18
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:04,410
-How many have you got?
-Ten.

19
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:05,995
Ten.

20
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:07,789
Alrighty.

21
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:10,541
Would you like
to do some postcards?

22
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:12,085
-Fifty cents per.
-Yeah.

23
00:04:13,169 --> 00:04:15,421
-Different pens, please.
-Okay.

24
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:19,842
Oh, Bubba.

25
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,846
Okay.

26
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:26,432
I like your passion.

27
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:28,810
But would you maybe
tone down the anger?

28
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:33,189
Make it that you're sad
that you even have to write the letter.

29
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:37,277
"I couldn't believe people could be
so heartless till I heard about you."

30
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:38,903
-Okay?
-Okay. Yeah, I got you.

31
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,780
-How many we got?
-Five.

32
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:44,284
-Would you like another batch?
-Yeah.

33
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:45,326
Yeah?

34
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,745
All right.

35
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,415
Different pens.

36
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:54,836
Chastity, let's see what you've got.

37
00:04:57,046 --> 00:05:00,091
Don't-- Don't use swears.

38
00:05:00,508 --> 00:05:02,802
I thought we talked about respect.

39
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:06,306
We're gonna have to lose that one.

40
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:14,934
I'm a little light.
Couldn't do nothing about it.

41
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:18,855
Some dumb-ass festival
over at the fairground, Indian shit.

42
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,356
Five-0 was all over.

43
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:22,316
But not real five-0, like, the rentals.

44
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:26,612
Can't sell in front of them neither.
We gonna make you right next time.

45
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,739
You're goddamned right you will.

46
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,950
For sure. Next week.

47
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:38,958
Hey.

48
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:41,210
Come here.

49
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:44,755
Nacho, man, I gotta get to getting--

50
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:47,425
Just come here.

51
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,600
What's up? What's up?

52
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,362
Shit.

53
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:29,050
What you owe, you owe.

54
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,177
With interest.

55
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,326
You had to do that, man.

56
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:58,579
Guy's not gonna learn otherwise.

57
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:01,791
So why didn't you do it?

58
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:10,508
What up, Domingo?

59
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:45,918
--can include headache, nausea,
dizziness and vision changes.

60
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:48,796
The Committee is the proper place--

61
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:53,217
But she wasn't the only witness that--

62
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:57,638
-I didn't see it right away, but--
-It's magic.

63
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:04,687
And I just wanna show you
the real difference with this.

64
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:07,982
If you wanna use the scrub too,
it's that same idea.

65
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:11,986
It's just that simple.
Smells like fresh lavender too, ladies.

66
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:15,281
- And you just will not....
-Hey, baby. You're in early.

67
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,199
You in for the night?

68
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,160
Want us to make you some dinner?

69
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:22,079
Takes the color right out.
And this bottle has smoothing agents...

70
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:24,540
...that protect your skin
while exfoliating.

71
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:26,292
Thanks, babe.

72
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:28,336
Are you gonna smoke with us?

73
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:32,840
Look at that. This vest, it's just--
Well, I think that's incredible.

74
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:37,762
And I cannot believe we're still
offering this for under $70.

75
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:39,555
There's no way that lasts.

76
00:13:35,815 --> 00:13:38,526
-Keep an eye on them.
-You got it.

77
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:55,459
Did you know, Michael,
my father was also an engineer?

78
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:56,669
Yeah.

79
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:59,338
Worked from the day
he could hold a hammer.

80
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:02,591
Learned the work from doing the work.

81
00:14:02,758 --> 00:14:05,928
Hands like knots of a tree.

82
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:09,181
You see over there?

83
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:10,724
He built that.

84
00:14:13,811 --> 00:14:15,980
The Sydney Opera House?

85
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:19,900
Those concrete arches,
impossible in 1957.

86
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:23,737
Six years it took
to solve the problem. Six.

87
00:14:23,904 --> 00:14:27,199
And years more to pour correctly.

88
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:31,912
To that, my father gave 10 years of life.

89
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:33,914
Another stout?

90
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:38,127
You know, could I get the
"Heefiweesen" this time?

91
00:14:38,294 --> 00:14:39,503
Sure.

92
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:43,757
No. Sir. Please. It's "Hefeweizen."

93
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:45,926
Oh, I'm sorry.

94
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:47,261
How did you say it?

95
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:48,929
Hefeweizen.

96
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:50,139
Hefeweizen.

97
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:51,932
That's right.

98
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,395
It's on me.

99
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,939
Thanks, man.

100
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,029
Prost.

101
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:09,533
Where was I?

102
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:10,868
The Opera.

103
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:12,870
It's for the ages.

104
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:15,915
For my father, it was his achievement.

105
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,833
A creation that will endure.

106
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:25,507
What about you, Michael?

107
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:27,843
Your papa, what did he do?

108
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:31,513
My dad?

109
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:39,855
Left behind a cold-water flat
and a stack of bills. That's about all.

110
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:41,482
Not true.

111
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:43,943
He also left you, Michael.

112
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:46,904
You are his legacy.

113
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:50,616
Yeah. You ever think about
having kids?

114
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,534
Being a papa yourself?

115
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,705
Once, maybe.

116
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:02,086
My Margarethe...

117
00:16:02,252 --> 00:16:05,547
...she's enough for me.

118
00:16:05,714 --> 00:16:06,966
She's my heart.

119
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:12,513
This is the longest
I've ever been away from her.

120
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:16,058
Twenty-six years...

121
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:19,895
...never this long away from home.

122
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:24,900
To home.

123
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,318
Yeah.

124
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,489
Hey, Mike.

125
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:39,581
I gotta check on the boys.
You gonna be all right here?

126
00:16:39,748 --> 00:16:41,166
Of course. I'll be fine. Go.

127
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:54,513
Sorry, Mike.
This guy slipped off for a private dance.

128
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,141
You're not throwing me out,
I paid my money.

129
00:16:57,307 --> 00:17:00,436
You paid to look, not touch, asshole.
That's it.

130
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:03,647
I'm calling the cops. Let's see how
you like hanging out in MDC.

131
00:17:03,814 --> 00:17:06,358
No, no, no.
You don't need to call the cops.

132
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:08,318
Who the hell are you?

133
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:10,654
I'm the guy telling you
this one's had too much...

134
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:12,698
...and I'm here
to get him out of your hair.

135
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,034
What about his buddies?

136
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,077
They're not causing
any trouble, are they?

137
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:19,747
Let them stay a while longer.

138
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:23,500
This one? This idiot goes home.

139
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,545
-Sleeps it off.
-No, no. I'm not going. I paid--

140
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:30,090
You are done.

141
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:35,929
Go on. Try me.

142
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,975
Get him out of here.

143
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,109
Sorry.

144
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:55,157
The girl, is she okay?

145
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,576
She's fine. Seen worse.

146
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:01,163
This is for her trouble.

147
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:05,084
All good?

148
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:07,878
Yeah, man. We're cool.

149
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:17,971
So....

150
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:21,642
Like this.

151
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:24,520
How about...?

152
00:18:27,147 --> 00:18:29,191
Nein, nein, nein,  Terry.

153
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:30,984
Support must be invisible.

154
00:18:31,151 --> 00:18:33,946
Can't throw a column here,
a column there.

155
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,865
Maximum volume
and open space inside.

156
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:42,246
The final structure
has strict requirements.

157
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:45,082
-Load-bearing walls, then.
-Very good.

158
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:47,584
Now you use your thinking head,
not your drinking head.

159
00:18:47,751 --> 00:18:49,753
But how do you get walls in place?

160
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,422
They would be seven,
eight meters to a side.

161
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:53,757
Pre-pour off site.

162
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:55,384
Slide the slabs in with a crane.

163
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:56,593
Slide?

164
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:59,304
Through the existing construction?

165
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:01,890
You would knock down
the Chrysler Building

166
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:04,226
just to add a subway stop.

167
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:05,394
No.

168
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:07,563
Time to go.

169
00:19:07,729 --> 00:19:10,607
Why? Come sit with us.

170
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:12,359
Your wife's calling.

171
00:19:12,526 --> 00:19:14,027
My wife?

172
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,405
Yeah.

173
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,577
Okay.

174
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:27,541
Thank you very much, gentlemen,
for your hospitality.

175
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,293
Good talking to you, Werner.

176
00:19:29,501 --> 00:19:31,336
See you.

177
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:19,801
Oh, hey. You say something?

178
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:21,845
Yeah, I'm gonna head over
to the nail salon.

179
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:23,222
Finish setting up.

180
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:25,933
Oh, that's a good idea. I'll see you later.

181
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:42,407
I won't be that long.

182
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,910
You want me to bring you something?
Maybe Flying Star?

183
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:48,205
I'm just gonna scrounge here.
I think we have some old Chinese.

184
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:50,040
Pick something up for yourself, okay?

185
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:52,876
-Yeah. Okay.
-All right.

186
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:26,451
Leaving now. You stick around?

187
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:29,496
Yeah, I have-- Be here a little longer.

188
00:21:29,663 --> 00:21:32,082
I'll lock up when I go.
Is that all right?

189
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,418
Wife mad at you?

190
00:21:34,584 --> 00:21:36,586
She's not my wife--

191
00:21:37,796 --> 00:21:39,298
I don’t know.

192
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:42,426
Yeah. She's mad at you.

193
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:06,116
Go on.

194
00:22:13,623 --> 00:22:15,042
You take her to dinner.

195
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:17,336
Nice place with a waiter.

196
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:18,670
Cloth napkin.

197
00:22:19,046 --> 00:22:20,881
You bring flowers.

198
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:23,091
You say sorry.

199
00:22:23,258 --> 00:22:24,676
Then say sorry again.

200
00:22:24,843 --> 00:22:27,804
Whatever she says, you say sorry.

201
00:22:29,514 --> 00:22:31,600
I think we might be past that.

202
00:22:37,981 --> 00:22:39,858
I'll leave the bottle.

203
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:17,354
Are you ready for me? I'm a little early.

204
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:19,106
No problem. Come on in.

205
00:23:20,941 --> 00:23:24,277
This is Gary Strote,
Stef Carvaines, Pat Malakovsky.

206
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:26,154
-My associates.
-Hi.

207
00:23:27,447 --> 00:23:28,782
-Suzanne Ericsen.
-Hello.

208
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:31,410
-Good to meet you all.
-Nice to meet you.

209
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:39,793
All right.
You have a response to our proffer?

210
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,169
We do. Time served.

211
00:23:41,628 --> 00:23:44,965
Three- to six-months' probation.
We plead to simple battery.

212
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:47,801
-A misdemeanor?
-Yes.

213
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:52,222
You're asking to go from
18-months' jail time down to nothing?

214
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,976
Sorry. I can't do that.

215
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:57,602
Okay.

216
00:23:58,937 --> 00:24:00,772
This is a motion for continuance.

217
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:03,692
We're going to need more time
to prepare our defense.

218
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:07,612
The officer's report states that he didn't
canvass for additional witnesses.

219
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:09,197
There were none.

220
00:24:09,364 --> 00:24:12,367
And no one is contesting that
Mr. Babineaux struck the officer.

221
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:15,620
Be that as it may, there are several
businesses nearby with cameras.

222
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:17,789
We need time to subpoena all of them.

223
00:24:18,665 --> 00:24:19,666
Isn't that a bit much?

224
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:21,793
We don't believe
the judge will see it that way.

225
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:25,797
We'd simply like to have the most
complete information at our disposal.

226
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:27,674
To that end...

227
00:24:28,258 --> 00:24:31,219
...we're filing a motion
to compel discovery.

228
00:24:33,054 --> 00:24:36,558
You want to open Officer Platt's
personnel file.

229
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:39,436
-Good luck with that.
-It's a reasonable Brady disclosure.

230
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:41,980
Officer Platt had a history with
Mr. Babineaux...

231
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:43,523
...we'd like to know its extent.

232
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:47,736
And if there's any larger history
Officer Platt has with friends, relatives...

233
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:51,114
...or colleagues of Mr. Babineaux,
we'd like to know that too.

234
00:24:51,281 --> 00:24:54,493
You're thinking
of pursuing civil litigation?

235
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:56,661
We are in conversation with the ACLU.

236
00:24:56,828 --> 00:24:59,414
Assessing the possibility that
Mr. Babineaux's civil rights...

237
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:01,333
...may have been violated.

238
00:25:04,669 --> 00:25:07,130
Okay. Is that all?

239
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:08,965
For now.

240
00:25:11,676 --> 00:25:15,055
We will deal with
all these issues in turn.

241
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:17,641
And then we will set a trial date.

242
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:20,644
I think that's all we have to talk about.

243
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:23,688
All right, then.

244
00:25:29,069 --> 00:25:31,196
Ms. Wexler, a word in private?

245
00:25:32,614 --> 00:25:34,074
I'll catch up.

246
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:46,211
Kim. You're throwing three $400-an-hour
associates at a pro-bono case?

247
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:48,713
I never said this was pro bono.

248
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:53,802
Okay, what's the plan here, Kim?

249
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:56,221
Because shock and awe
isn't gonna cut it.

250
00:25:56,972 --> 00:26:00,976
Bring every fancy associate you got,
file all the motions you want.

251
00:26:01,142 --> 00:26:05,146
And at the end of all this,
your client is still going away.

252
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:08,316
Okay.

253
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:11,736
I guess we'll see.

254
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:58,867
Everyone seems much improved.

255
00:26:59,242 --> 00:27:03,788
This R&R was a good idea, Michael.

256
00:27:08,543 --> 00:27:10,295
Something the matter?

257
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:18,887
This?

258
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:22,098
Don't be concerned.

259
00:27:22,265 --> 00:27:23,725
I said nothing.

260
00:27:23,892 --> 00:27:25,977
Men at a bar, talking to make talk.

261
00:27:26,144 --> 00:27:27,437
And look.

262
00:27:27,604 --> 00:27:29,981
No details. No scale at all.

263
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:34,611
Could be a skyscraper,
could be a box for shoes.

264
00:27:37,864 --> 00:27:42,952
I said nothing about the construction
that would not be true for 1000 others.

265
00:27:43,536 --> 00:27:45,914
By now they've forgotten me entirely.

266
00:27:46,081 --> 00:27:47,874
They forgot.

267
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:52,253
The German national
in the middle of Albuquerque...

268
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:55,507
...talking about pouring
hundreds of tons of concrete...

269
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:58,385
...at a secret underground location?

270
00:27:59,969 --> 00:28:01,846
You're right.

271
00:28:02,305 --> 00:28:05,475
I'm sorry, Michael. I had too much beer.

272
00:28:05,809 --> 00:28:09,145
And I may have said
more than I should have.

273
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:14,150
Listen to me carefully.

274
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:18,571
The man we're working for
is very serious.

275
00:28:18,988 --> 00:28:23,243
Think about the precautions we take
to keep everything that goes on quiet.

276
00:28:23,660 --> 00:28:26,663
Think about how much money
you're making.

277
00:28:26,955 --> 00:28:30,333
Think about what happens
if something goes wrong.

278
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:35,296
Do you understand
what I am saying to you?

279
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:41,720
I do understand.

280
00:28:44,097 --> 00:28:46,433
And I'm sorry to cause any problem.

281
00:28:47,225 --> 00:28:48,977
You have my word.

282
00:28:49,602 --> 00:28:52,230
Nothing like this will happen again.

283
00:29:03,032 --> 00:29:04,409
Okay.

284
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:08,288
Let's get you to work.

285
00:29:15,628 --> 00:29:18,465
I have one question for you,
Ms. Ericsen.

286
00:29:18,631 --> 00:29:21,301
-Are you prosecuting Santa Claus?
-Your Honor?

287
00:29:21,468 --> 00:29:24,053
Because it's like
Miracle on 34th Street  in here.

288
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,555
This is just today.

289
00:29:26,014 --> 00:29:27,724
Today's batch.

290
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:29,392
All addressed to me.

291
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:32,937
All from some backwater in Louisiana.

292
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,648
"Get your hands off our hero," they say.

293
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:37,901
"Mercy for Huell Babineaux," they say.

294
00:29:38,067 --> 00:29:40,737
Like I'm sending him
to the electric chair.

295
00:29:40,904 --> 00:29:44,824
Tell me, Ms. Wexler,
did you start this particular ball rolling?

296
00:29:44,991 --> 00:29:47,285
Did I instruct the people of
Coushatta, Louisiana...

297
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:51,664
...to start writing letters to the court?
No, Your Honor, I did not.

298
00:29:52,165 --> 00:29:56,628
That being said, it's clear Mr. Babineaux
has touched the lives...

299
00:29:56,795 --> 00:29:58,797
...of many people in his hometown.

300
00:29:58,963 --> 00:30:02,675
They're planning to send a contingent.
To show their support during the trial.

301
00:30:02,842 --> 00:30:05,220
Are you talking about a bunch
of yahoos packing my court?

302
00:30:05,386 --> 00:30:09,933
I'm sorry, Your Honor, but I'm not sure
what bearing any of this has on the case.

303
00:30:10,099 --> 00:30:13,520
What does Mr. Babineaux's relationship
to his hometown in--?

304
00:30:13,686 --> 00:30:14,813
Did you say Louisiana?

305
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:18,358
This can't be a complete surprise
to the assistant district attorney.

306
00:30:18,525 --> 00:30:20,777
She knows the defendant's history
as well as I do.

307
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:24,280
If I get one more letter
from some swamp-dwelling do-gooder...

308
00:30:24,405 --> 00:30:26,366
-...I'm gonna scream.
-Thank you...

309
00:30:26,533 --> 00:30:28,326
...for bringing this to our attention.

310
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,787
May I see one of these?

311
00:30:30,954 --> 00:30:32,789
Take as many as you want. Yeah.

312
00:30:32,956 --> 00:30:34,791
Please. Take them all.

313
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:36,626
I have looked at this case.

314
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:38,461
It does not merit a circus.

315
00:30:38,628 --> 00:30:40,213
Now, you two work it out.

316
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:44,092
-We've tried, Your Honor.
-Try again.

317
00:30:47,637 --> 00:30:49,264
Pull the Babineaux file.

318
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:53,560
Every parking ticket, every time
he is mentioned in the records.

319
00:30:53,726 --> 00:30:55,645
You, call the arresting officer...

320
00:30:55,812 --> 00:30:58,606
...and find out what, if anything,
he left out of his reports.

321
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:02,569
I want known associates.
Places of residence.

322
00:31:02,735 --> 00:31:04,988
MVD records. All of it.

323
00:31:05,154 --> 00:31:08,199
We missed something,
and I wanna know what.

324
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:10,577
Right now. Go.

325
00:31:11,452 --> 00:31:12,620
Ben.

326
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:16,207
What are we looking for?

327
00:31:16,374 --> 00:31:21,838
I want to figure out why a pickpocket
has people this overheated.

328
00:31:33,641 --> 00:31:36,144
"Huell Babineaux
is wrongfully accused.

329
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:37,562
He's a good man.

330
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:40,106
He'd never do nothing like the things
you say he's done.

331
00:31:40,273 --> 00:31:42,150
He's a kind man
and good friend to everyone."

332
00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:44,360
Jesus. They do make him sound
like Santa Claus.

333
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:47,739
-This one has a phone number.
-Let me see this.

334
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:00,585
You've reached Elmer Fontaneau.

335
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:03,129
I'm not here at the moment,
but leave a message...

336
00:32:03,296 --> 00:32:06,382
...I'll get back at you soon as I can.
Have a blessed day.

337
00:32:06,841 --> 00:32:08,051
Hello, Mr. Fontaneau.

338
00:32:08,217 --> 00:32:13,097
My name is Suzanne Ericsen from
the Albuquerque district attorney's office.

339
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:15,516
Could you give me a call
when you have a moment?

340
00:32:15,683 --> 00:32:17,685
It's in regards to Huell Babineaux.

341
00:32:17,852 --> 00:32:23,524
My number is 505-186-1945.

342
00:32:23,691 --> 00:32:24,776
Thanks.

343
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:42,502
-Hello?
-Is this Eloise Luckard?

344
00:32:42,669 --> 00:32:46,339
-Speaking.
-Hi, my name is Suzanne Ericsen.

345
00:32:46,506 --> 00:32:50,760
I'm an assistant district attorney
in Albuquerque, New Mexico.

346
00:32:50,927 --> 00:32:55,056
You wrote a letter to Judge Munsinger
about a Huell Babineaux.

347
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:57,392
Oh, I love Huell.

348
00:32:57,558 --> 00:33:00,144
He's the dearest, dearest man.

349
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:04,482
Do you mind my asking,
how exactly do you know Huell?

350
00:33:04,649 --> 00:33:06,651
Everyone in Coushatta knows Huell.

351
00:33:06,818 --> 00:33:09,862
-He's a pillar of our church.
-Which church is that?

352
00:33:10,029 --> 00:33:13,366
Free Will Baptist,
right over on Bogan Lane.

353
00:33:13,950 --> 00:33:18,871
I've seen several letters from
fellow members of your congregation.

354
00:33:19,038 --> 00:33:23,001
Could you explain to me,
is there some reason why Huell...

355
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:26,629
...in particular holds so much esteem
in your church?

356
00:33:28,047 --> 00:33:31,718
I'm sorry, who are you again?

357
00:33:31,884 --> 00:33:36,264
I'm an assistant district attorney
from Albuquerque, New Mexico.

358
00:33:36,431 --> 00:33:38,850
I'm handling a case that Mr. Babineaux
is involved in.

359
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:41,894
Handling how?

360
00:33:43,396 --> 00:33:45,356
I'm prosecuting it.

361
00:33:45,523 --> 00:33:49,444
You're the one persecuting our Huell?
How could you?

362
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:54,449
To go after someone so sweet
and kind with all those lies.

363
00:33:55,033 --> 00:33:58,202
Well, I'd tell you
what I really think of you...

364
00:33:58,369 --> 00:34:05,043
...but Jesus is listening,
so I'll just say shame on you.

365
00:34:07,253 --> 00:34:09,172
Okay.

366
00:34:10,298 --> 00:34:11,424
All right.

367
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:13,760
Not too shabby.

368
00:34:14,093 --> 00:34:17,055
I've been taking improv classes.

369
00:34:32,945 --> 00:34:34,947
Oh, shit. Which one is it?

370
00:34:35,114 --> 00:34:36,616
It's that one.

371
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:41,037
It's the church. The church, the church.

372
00:34:42,371 --> 00:34:43,706
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

373
00:34:51,297 --> 00:34:54,383
Hello, there. Free Will Baptist,
Pastor Hansford speaking.

374
00:34:54,842 --> 00:34:56,844
- Who this?
-Good afternoon, Pastor.

375
00:34:57,011 --> 00:34:58,721
My name is Suzanne Ericsen.

376
00:34:58,888 --> 00:35:01,724
I'm an assistant district attorney
from Albuquerque, New Mexico.

377
00:35:01,891 --> 00:35:05,353
Oh, that's a long way off,  cher.

378
00:35:05,561 --> 00:35:09,690
Can you hold on a second?
Clarence is going at the organ.

379
00:35:11,025 --> 00:35:13,611
I'm gonna step into the vestibule.

380
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:16,030
There we go.

381
00:35:16,197 --> 00:35:21,410
Now, what can I do for you,
Ms. Ericsen, you say?

382
00:35:22,537 --> 00:35:25,915
The court has received numerous
letters from members...

383
00:35:26,082 --> 00:35:30,294
...of your congregation in regards to
Mr. Huell Babineaux.

384
00:35:30,628 --> 00:35:33,756
May I ask you a couple questions
about Mr. Babineaux?

385
00:35:33,923 --> 00:35:36,801
Surely. What I can tell you
about our Huell?

386
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:41,139
Well, what kind of person
would you say Mr. Babineaux is?

387
00:35:41,305 --> 00:35:46,978
Why, I'd say he's a lovely person,
both inside and out.

388
00:35:47,145 --> 00:35:50,148
I'm sure you'd say that about
all your parishioners.

389
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:52,441
Right. I suppose I would.

390
00:35:52,608 --> 00:35:55,778
No, no. But Huell, he's special.

391
00:35:55,945 --> 00:35:59,365
He's got a heart as big as
Lake Pontchartrain.

392
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:03,911
Do you mind my asking,
what did he do...

393
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:07,582
...to gain so much devotion
in Coushatta?

394
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:10,501
Well, ma'am, for starters...

395
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,920
...he's a bona fide hero.

396
00:36:13,671 --> 00:36:15,840
-He's a hero?
- Yes, ma'am.

397
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:20,428
See, about a year ago,
there was a fire in the rectory.

398
00:36:20,595 --> 00:36:23,014
It was during Bible study.

399
00:36:23,556 --> 00:36:24,557
At night.

400
00:36:24,724 --> 00:36:28,019
Because some of the old folks
around here...

401
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:31,981
...they like to brush up on the Bible
before they go to sleep.

402
00:36:32,148 --> 00:36:36,152
You know, get right
in case the Lord call them home.

403
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:38,112
-Yes.
- Wouldn't you know it...

404
00:36:38,279 --> 00:36:40,990
...there was a
short circuit in the coffeemaker.

405
00:36:41,157 --> 00:36:45,369
Whole thing catch fire, and the flame
leaped up to the window sill.

406
00:36:45,912 --> 00:36:50,499
Well, Huell happened to be visiting
his people, and he saw the smoke.

407
00:36:50,666 --> 00:36:52,627
Well, what did he do?

408
00:36:52,793 --> 00:36:54,378
He burst right in.

409
00:36:54,545 --> 00:36:57,298
Carried out
every last one of them oldsters.

410
00:36:57,465 --> 00:36:58,591
My goodness.

411
00:36:58,966 --> 00:37:01,427
And what happened to the church?

412
00:37:01,594 --> 00:37:03,262
The church is fine.

413
00:37:06,098 --> 00:37:09,602
I shudder to think
what might've happened if God...

414
00:37:09,769 --> 00:37:13,564
...in his grace hadn't seen fit
to send us old Huell.

415
00:37:13,731 --> 00:37:14,941
I see.

416
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:19,946
Now, y'all sound like a real nice lady,
and I know you're only doing your job.

417
00:37:20,112 --> 00:37:22,448
But I want you
to understand something.

418
00:37:22,615 --> 00:37:25,076
I think you got the wrong end
of the stick here.

419
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,328
Huell Babineaux is important to us.

420
00:37:27,495 --> 00:37:28,955
Now, he--

421
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:32,250
He would never hurt a police officer.

422
00:37:32,416 --> 00:37:35,086
I believe it's just a misunderstanding.

423
00:37:35,253 --> 00:37:37,797
I believe he might've been
helping his friend.

424
00:37:37,964 --> 00:37:40,591
That's the Huell that I know.

425
00:37:42,051 --> 00:37:43,302
Put that down, Clarence.

426
00:37:43,469 --> 00:37:45,972
Get rid of them robes, now.
That's for communion.

427
00:37:46,138 --> 00:37:48,349
Now, I will be with you presently.

428
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:51,477
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

429
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:54,313
No. No, Pastor.
Thank you for your time.

430
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:56,232
I think that's all.

431
00:37:56,649 --> 00:38:00,486
Have you set a date yet
for Huell's trial?

432
00:38:01,153 --> 00:38:02,321
No, not yet.

433
00:38:02,488 --> 00:38:07,326
Would you do me a kindness
and ring me up when you do?

434
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:09,787
Because we got a couple of
charter buses.

435
00:38:10,621 --> 00:38:15,042
We're gonna bring the whole
congregation up to y'all in Albuquerque.

436
00:38:16,877 --> 00:38:18,504
I'll make sure to let you know.

437
00:38:19,088 --> 00:38:20,089
Bless you.

438
00:38:20,256 --> 00:38:22,258
And I look forward to meeting you.

439
00:38:47,450 --> 00:38:49,118
Is it over?

440
00:38:53,956 --> 00:38:55,333
All right.

441
00:38:55,583 --> 00:38:59,670
Here's what we're gonna do.
I'm gonna take the church phone.

442
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:01,047
She might call back.

443
00:39:01,213 --> 00:39:07,094
If any of these ring,
I want you to pick up every third caller.

444
00:39:07,261 --> 00:39:12,099
Okay? Thirty seconds max,
stick to the script.

445
00:39:12,266 --> 00:39:14,268
Let the rest go to voicemail.

446
00:39:16,145 --> 00:39:17,980
So are we just supposed to...

447
00:39:18,147 --> 00:39:20,232
...hang around here till...?

448
00:39:20,399 --> 00:39:23,110
You're paid for the day,
you stay until I say you can go.

449
00:40:12,326 --> 00:40:13,786
Well?

450
00:40:28,968 --> 00:40:30,261
Do it one more time?

451
00:40:30,428 --> 00:40:32,430
You sure you can take it?

452
00:40:32,596 --> 00:40:34,181
I can if you can.

453
00:40:34,348 --> 00:40:37,393
All right. You asked for it.

454
00:40:37,852 --> 00:40:39,437
Hello there.

455
00:40:39,603 --> 00:40:42,648
Look in your heart,
cher,  and find forgiveness.

456
00:40:42,815 --> 00:40:46,068
Let us take you on a trip
down New Orleans way...

457
00:40:46,235 --> 00:40:49,321
...where they put a little extra roux
in the gumbo.

458
00:40:49,488 --> 00:40:52,533
Oh, that's a beautiful red snapper.

459
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:55,286
It's wondermous, I guarantee.

460
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,496
Wow, it's like I'm in the bayou.

461
00:40:57,663 --> 00:41:00,708
Yes, well, I got crawdads in my pants.

462
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:06,505
-That's not a thing.
-It's a thing that happens to you...

463
00:41:06,672 --> 00:41:09,008
...when you're sitting in the bayou.

464
00:41:11,510 --> 00:41:13,220
The phones were genius.

465
00:41:13,387 --> 00:41:15,473
-The phones?
-Yeah.

466
00:41:16,182 --> 00:41:19,226
Well, the phones were a touch.

467
00:41:19,393 --> 00:41:21,770
This was all you, start to finish.

468
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:24,190
Bank shot off the judge.

469
00:41:24,356 --> 00:41:27,610
Four months' probation, time served.

470
00:41:27,776 --> 00:41:31,655
It's like watching Roy Hobbs
smash out stadium lights.

471
00:41:31,822 --> 00:41:34,867
Yeah, but the DA overplayed her hand.

472
00:41:35,034 --> 00:41:36,452
Yeah.

473
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:44,335
Gotta go?

474
00:41:44,502 --> 00:41:45,794
Yeah.

475
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:50,424
What are you up to today?

476
00:41:51,967 --> 00:41:56,680
I'm gonna check out an office
on Lomas, down by the courthouse.

477
00:41:56,847 --> 00:41:58,807
I thought you already found one.

478
00:41:58,974 --> 00:42:03,103
That one was a little more office
than I needed.

479
00:42:05,981 --> 00:42:07,900
You working late?

480
00:42:10,903 --> 00:42:12,738
Playing catch up.

481
00:42:15,908 --> 00:42:17,076
All right.

482
00:42:17,243 --> 00:42:18,702
I gotta go.

483
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:21,038
I gotta go, I gotta go.

484
00:42:37,638 --> 00:42:40,641
The near-term window is set,
but we have to hit every target...

485
00:42:40,808 --> 00:42:42,268
...to stick to that timetable.

486
00:42:42,434 --> 00:42:45,396
As we look down the road,
we get more flexibility.

487
00:42:45,563 --> 00:42:48,190
When we get to rollouts
in the six- to 12-month timeline...

488
00:42:48,357 --> 00:42:50,734
...and beyond,
we have some breathing room.

489
00:42:50,901 --> 00:42:54,780
It's an opportunity to retrench and
meet our minimum capital requirements.

490
00:42:54,947 --> 00:42:57,825
We should be stable as a table
by the time we start on Wyoming.

491
00:42:58,200 --> 00:42:59,493
Sounds good.

492
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:01,161
We should talk about Wyoming.

493
00:43:01,328 --> 00:43:03,622
Six months is gonna go by fast.

494
00:43:06,959 --> 00:43:11,255
Unless, Kevin,
did you have something?

495
00:43:11,547 --> 00:43:16,343
Sorry. I don't wanna slow us down.
Paige will hate me for bringing this up.

496
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:20,848
What's on your mind?

497
00:43:21,181 --> 00:43:23,350
The foot traffic
at Tucumcari is off the charts...

498
00:43:23,517 --> 00:43:25,644
...and that's driving
a lot of new accounts.

499
00:43:25,811 --> 00:43:29,231
Seems to me it's because
the building itself is damn eye-catching.

500
00:43:29,398 --> 00:43:32,151
Now, I want to hit all the milestones
we're talking about.

501
00:43:32,318 --> 00:43:36,155
And Paige tells me
what I'm gonna ask is impossible...

502
00:43:37,615 --> 00:43:40,284
...but what if we made the Lubbock
branch the same as Tucumcari?

503
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:43,537
I reminded Kevin that Tucumcari
has a much larger footprint...

504
00:43:43,704 --> 00:43:45,289
...than the current Lubbock design.

505
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:48,375
And that design is the one
we've been hanging our estimates on.

506
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:51,295
I know, I know.
We're down the road a ways on this.

507
00:43:52,755 --> 00:43:54,465
But what do you think, Kim?

508
00:43:54,632 --> 00:43:57,426
Can you pull another rabbit
out of the hat for us?

509
00:44:00,012 --> 00:44:03,265
Kevin, I'm sorry.

510
00:44:04,141 --> 00:44:06,018
But I have to agree with Paige.

511
00:44:06,352 --> 00:44:10,898
It took almost two months to get
local approval for the current design.

512
00:44:11,065 --> 00:44:12,524
Starting over now?

513
00:44:12,691 --> 00:44:15,944
There's simply no way
we could stick to our timetable.

514
00:44:16,362 --> 00:44:18,405
I hate to say it...

515
00:44:19,073 --> 00:44:20,908
...but it is. It's unfeasible.

516
00:44:21,909 --> 00:44:23,160
Okay.

517
00:44:23,327 --> 00:44:25,120
I get it. I had to ask.

518
00:44:26,121 --> 00:44:28,332
Paige, you were right. This time.

519
00:44:28,499 --> 00:44:31,293
All right. Wyoming, then.

520
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:33,921
Yellowstone, here we come.

521
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:35,297
Great.

522
00:44:35,464 --> 00:44:37,383
So looking to Wyoming...

523
00:44:37,549 --> 00:44:40,511
...we are moving forward
with market research, as planned.

524
00:45:12,334 --> 00:45:15,003
Space is closing in
on rough final dimensions.

525
00:45:15,170 --> 00:45:17,214
Most of the spoil's out and dispersed.

526
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:19,758
The tunnel's holding and it's clear.

527
00:45:19,925 --> 00:45:24,138
The front loader
hit this support stanchion.

528
00:45:24,304 --> 00:45:26,306
Guys had it back up in an hour.

529
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:28,267
No permanent damage.

530
00:45:28,642 --> 00:45:32,980
Then the form
they use to pour cement into...

531
00:45:33,147 --> 00:45:34,606
...it's totaled.

532
00:45:34,773 --> 00:45:38,527
We're gonna have to make a new one
before we can go back to the wall.

533
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:42,448
So we're looking at four,
maybe five days for that.

534
00:45:42,614 --> 00:45:44,491
Could’ve been worse.

535
00:45:45,993 --> 00:45:49,955
The rock, that is more of an issue.

536
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:53,709
It is smack-dab in the middle
of our elevator shaft.

537
00:45:53,876 --> 00:45:56,295
Can't work around it, can't dig it out.

538
00:45:56,462 --> 00:45:57,963
So we're back to blasting.

539
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:03,135
Set up, clearing away debris...

540
00:46:03,844 --> 00:46:05,512
...adds maybe another week.

541
00:46:06,597 --> 00:46:09,391
Best estimate,
we're a little past the halfway point.

542
00:46:09,558 --> 00:46:13,520
Way behind schedule,
but the work is solid.

543
00:46:16,315 --> 00:46:18,025
And Werner?

544
00:46:20,194 --> 00:46:22,780
I gave him the "come-to-Jesus."

545
00:46:22,946 --> 00:46:25,199
He screwed up. He knows it.

546
00:46:25,365 --> 00:46:27,075
Said it won't happen again.

547
00:46:29,244 --> 00:46:31,121
And what do you say?

548
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:35,042
I've got eyes on him.

549
00:46:35,209 --> 00:46:37,586
But, yeah, he's good.

550
00:46:44,092 --> 00:46:45,511
Good.

551
00:46:55,395 --> 00:46:56,814
Is that water?

552
00:46:56,980 --> 00:46:59,691
The landlord will kick in
for small repairs like that.

553
00:46:59,858 --> 00:47:02,110
They already took care
of the rodent problem.

554
00:47:02,611 --> 00:47:04,321
Rodent problem?

555
00:47:04,488 --> 00:47:07,491
You asked for small and near court.
This is both.

556
00:47:08,075 --> 00:47:09,910
And it's in your price range.

557
00:47:10,077 --> 00:47:12,162
Use your imagination.

558
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:14,164
Think creatively.

559
00:47:16,375 --> 00:47:18,001
Excuse me for a sec, would you?

560
00:47:18,168 --> 00:47:19,920
Yeah. Take your time.

561
00:47:25,342 --> 00:47:26,468
Hey.

562
00:47:26,635 --> 00:47:28,011
Hey.

563
00:47:28,178 --> 00:47:30,097
This your new office?

564
00:47:30,806 --> 00:47:32,349
It's a contender.

565
00:47:33,475 --> 00:47:35,435
What are you doing here?

566
00:47:36,311 --> 00:47:37,563
I was driving.

567
00:47:38,564 --> 00:47:41,108
Saw your Esteem in the parking lot.

568
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:48,490
So, what's up?

569
00:47:49,616 --> 00:47:51,076
Nothing.

570
00:47:52,995 --> 00:47:54,872
Just driving around.

571
00:47:55,038 --> 00:47:56,999
Thinking about things.

572
00:48:00,669 --> 00:48:04,423
Listen, Kim, I--
I know what's on your mind.

573
00:48:05,173 --> 00:48:08,302
That thing that we did,
I mean, it was nuts.

574
00:48:10,762 --> 00:48:13,432
And I dumped it in your lap.

575
00:48:14,182 --> 00:48:16,268
Ex parte communication...

576
00:48:16,435 --> 00:48:18,145
...contempt of court.

577
00:48:18,312 --> 00:48:21,356
I mean, what, talking about
a couple hundred counts of mail fraud?

578
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:24,776
I could've wrecked you at Schweikart.
I could've boned me too.

579
00:48:24,943 --> 00:48:27,362
I'm this close to being reinstated.

580
00:48:27,529 --> 00:48:29,489
I mean, come on.

581
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:34,453
Kim.

582
00:48:36,121 --> 00:48:38,582
Don't worry.
No one's gonna know about it.

583
00:48:38,749 --> 00:48:40,375
Be like it never happened.

584
00:48:40,542 --> 00:48:42,711
And also, I agree.

585
00:48:42,878 --> 00:48:45,714
We are totally done with all that.

586
00:48:45,881 --> 00:48:47,090
Over and out.

587
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:49,718
No more.

588
00:48:58,852 --> 00:49:00,562
Let's do it again.

589
00:50:04,251 --> 00:50:06,044
Oh, hey.

590
00:50:06,211 --> 00:50:08,213
You're here! Right on time.

591
00:50:08,380 --> 00:50:10,298
Hold on one second. Wait.

592
00:50:10,716 --> 00:50:14,219
You are going to love this.

593
00:50:14,386 --> 00:50:16,013
I made this just for you.

594
00:50:16,179 --> 00:50:20,350
Never in your life have you tasted
something so delicious, it's true. Wait....

595
00:50:21,601 --> 00:50:23,103
You're gonna die.

596
00:50:26,440 --> 00:50:27,733
No, thank you.

597
00:50:30,444 --> 00:50:32,112
Smell it!

598
00:50:32,279 --> 00:50:34,197
You can't say no, are you crazy?

599
00:50:34,364 --> 00:50:36,867
I used  epazote.  Come on.

600
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:41,121
Very well. You're not hungry.

601
00:50:41,705 --> 00:50:42,914
That's your problem.

602
00:50:43,707 --> 00:50:48,670
This is a special recipe.
A family secret.

603
00:50:51,965 --> 00:50:53,592
-The Salamanca family?
-Them!

604
00:50:55,969 --> 00:50:56,970
I am Eduardo.

605
00:50:57,137 --> 00:50:58,638
But you can call me Lalo.

606
00:50:58,805 --> 00:51:02,184
And you must be Varga, no?

607
00:51:03,477 --> 00:51:06,521
They told me you were smart.
And look...

608
00:51:06,688 --> 00:51:09,524
...here you are, and you are.

609
00:51:17,783 --> 00:51:19,451
What are you doing here?

610
00:51:19,618 --> 00:51:21,203
I'm just here to lend a helping hand.

611
00:51:21,369 --> 00:51:24,289
Make sure business
is running in order.

612
00:51:25,248 --> 00:51:28,502
I got-- I got a good head for numbers.

613
00:51:28,752 --> 00:51:30,170
But listen...

614
00:51:30,754 --> 00:51:32,756
...don't even worry.

615
00:51:32,923 --> 00:51:35,008
It's gonna be like I'm not even here.

616
00:51:39,596 --> 00:51:41,431
Come on, Varga. Let's go!

